1. How to clone an existing remote repository?
git clone -b branchName repositoryURL


2. How to add an remote origin server to an local repository?
1. create an remote repository on the git server
for eg.. https://github.com/techsriman/guaragetools.git
remote repository should not have any commits

2. create an local repository
mkdir repodir
cd repodir
git init
touch README.md
git add .
git commit -m "comment"
git branch -M master
git remote add origin remoteRepositoryURL
git push -u origin master
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. How to see the remote origin server of an local repository?
git remote show origin

4. How to push the local repository changes into the remote server?
git push

5. How to get the new commits from remote repository into the local?
git pull

How to create a branch while working with remote repositories?
There are 2 ways are there
1. create remote branch
2. git pull
3. git checkout newbranch































